Sometimes I wish paint selections went this fast 🥲

Bringing a space to life with color is a a lot of where I started and something I still really love to do 🖤. 
I have four main paint decks that are on a constant rotation and I always, always, base my paint options off of the flooring going into a space and use really good lighting when selecting. This is super important, the same paint color will look different in every space depending on how much natural lights comes in and what type of bulbs are in the room.

Every year, just to stress my entire team out, I take on a handful of Parade Homes. For 12 months, we design the spaces and plan all of the furniture, decor and everything in between for each home. This year, we had three.

The last three weeks are 24/7 solid. It’s somewhat of a organized chaotic method of coordinating installs, consuming maximum amounts of caffeine on minimal amounts of sleep, moving furniture and decor across town hundreds of times (only to move it back again), installing so.much.art and laughing until we cried. Yes, we literally cried from laughing. 

This year, I asked @woodsbootcitylubbock to stage one of the master closets for us. During the very last hour at our third and last install, we decided we needed to test a few things out. Now, we aren’t the honkiest tonkiest cowgirls out there, but we sure know how to make each other laugh 🤠

I’ve read that people who love purple, often think about it, talk about it, have it everywhere around them…. Some would say the same about my love for black. But I dream and talk about color daily (as you can tell by my socks in the last picture). It truly brings life into a space. 

I remember how much I loved purple on my youngest when she was a baby. It was just perfect in her. And again in this project, the client loves purple. And color. Which made me oh so happy 🫶🏻.

It has stuck with me over the past year and I love seeing it pop up lately in deep, earthy tones. Makes me truly excited for what’s to come in 2024 💜.
